entries.album: The Dark Side of The Moon

entries.review: Beautiful, beautiful, beautiful. Makes me want to get way better at the guitar.  I think I will listen to this album forever and show my children someday. Favorite song: Place to Be.
This album feels like going back to my hometown and finding beauty in a place that is otherwise decrepit and awful. Or not really beauty, but accepting it for what it is. Favorite song is Quarry.
Warhol banana album. I listened to this while eating grocery sushi with the California sun on my back, which was quite beautiful. Incredible listen. Favorite song is There She Goes Again.
I have listened so much already. Quite perfect and I am seeing live today. Favorite song is Pick up That Knife.
I WISH I WAS STEPHEN MALKMUS. Favorite song: Silence Kid.
I like when an album is funny and makes me feel like someone I will never be. Favorite song: Rudolph.
I listen to this album all the timeâ€”I think it's going to become one of my favorites ever soon. Favorite song is $0.
The songs kind of all sound the same, but there are some bangers. Good songs to learn for beginner guitar. Favorite song is smaller acts.
This used to hit a lot harder when I was far sadder, but still great. It's like she was in my room. Favorite song is 16 even though I can't listen to it.
Not really an album but so good. Incredible songwriting it just blows my mind. Favorite song is Your Cat.
I MISS MODERN BASEBALL. Favorite song is The Weekend.
Very fun and silly. Favorite song Tastes Just Like It Costs.
Incredibly underrated album, I wish more people talked about it. Other than Harlem River Blues my favorite song is One More Night in Brooklyn.
Zach Bryan is an incredible songwriter, sometimes a bit overwrought. Favorite song is Like Ida.
Wonderful and weird. Makes me cry, makes me laugh. Everything I ever dreamed and more. Favorite song right now is Bow Down.
